article_title: Rick Holmes: Kasich is the anti-Trump
article_text:
By Rick Holmes

More Content Now

article_metadata.description: When Donald J. Trump campaigned in Worcester, Massachusetts a couple of months ago, he performed in the DCU Center, an arena big enough for hockey and monster truck competitions. The line to get in stretched for blocks as everyone went through Secret Service screening. When John Kasich went there last week, he packed a much smaller venue: the Hibernian Cultural Center, which is basically a bar and function room less than a mile from the DCU. Everyone was free to walk right in, no metal
